I":<p><i>The Hard Thing About Hard Things</i> chronicles the challenges that author Ben Horowitz encountered during his career from founder CEO to venture capitalist at Andreessen Horowitz. The book provides pragmatic advice to run, grow, and sustain a successful start-up. It begins by providing Ben’s backstory which he uses to teach the lesson on the importance of embracing one’s background and using it to their advantage. Then the story transitions to his experiences as a founder with valuable insights to anyone who is or wants to be a leader at a company.</p>
